div.p:
On August 17 a meeting was held in the office of Mr. Gerig (UND)
                    to discuss US strategy in the General Assembly in dealing with a threatened
                    Indian move to have the GA recommend a cessation
                    of nuclear tests in the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands pending an ICJ opinion on the legality of those tests.
                    Participating in the meeting were the following: 




                            L/UNA—Mr.
                                Fensterwald, 

Mrs. Fleming;




                            L/FE—Miss
                                Fite;


                            EUR—Mr. Allen;


                            ARA—Mr. Monsma;


                            UND—Mr. Gerig, 

Mr. Ross,

Mr. Withers;




                            UNP—Mr. Bechhoefer, 

Mr. Meyers;




                            NEA—Mr. Howard.
